<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4610768>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 11. Temnocyon cf. T. subferox (LACM 470), right mandible with p3–m2, damaged c, p1–2, from Kew Quarry, Sespe Formation, Ventura Co., California. This is the only record of the subfamily in western North America other than fossils from the John Day region." ;
